    ),
    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided text, here are the user, engagement, and "Family" metrics disclosed for the Family of Apps in 2025. \n\n### 1. Daily Active People (DAP)\n* **Definition:** A registered and logged-in user of Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, and/or WhatsApp who visited at least one of these products via a mobile app or web/mobile browser on a given day. The company uses machine learning and data signals to deduplicate accounts across apps and count unique individuals.\n* **2025 Data:** Worldwide DAP averaged **3.58 billion** in December 2025, representing a **7% year-over-year increase** (up from 3.35 billion in December 2024).\n* **Limitations:** The company notes an estimated error margin of approximately **3%** for worldwide DAP due to the complexities of attributing multiple accounts to single individuals across encrypted and non-encrypted apps.\n\n### 2. Violating Accounts\n* **Definition:** Accounts believed to be intended for purposes that violate terms of service, such as bots and spam. \n* **2025 Data:** In the fourth quarter of 2025, Meta estimated that **less than 5%** of its worldwide DAP consisted solely of violating accounts (an increase from prior estimations due to methodology updates and improved data signals).\n\n### 3. Average Revenue Per Person (ARPP)\n* *Note: While technically a monetization metric, the text explicitly groups ARPP with DAP under the umbrella of "Family metrics."*\n* **Definition:** Family of Apps (FoA) revenue during a given quarter, divided by the average number of DAP at the beginning and end of the quarter.\n* **2025 Data:** The text provides a quarterly data table for ARPP (values include $12.33, $11.20, $11.89, $12.29, $14.25, $12.36, $13.65, $14.46, and $16.56). \n\n### 4. Advertising Engagement Metrics\nWhile not strictly "user base" metrics, these engagement-driven advertising metrics are tied to user activity:\n* **Ad Impressions:** Increased by **12% year-over-year** in 2025 across the Family of App